Japan 's Cabinet Office announced the fourth - quarter Gross Domestic Product information for 2005 on Friday . 
After price adjustments , the actual increase in the quarter from October to December had increased by 1.4 percent compared to the last quarter , higher than the 1.2 percent expected . 
The main factors were the strong domestic demand and the growth in exports to major countries such as China and the United States . It had shown a sign of continuous economic recovery . 
This was the fourth consecutive quarter that Japan had showed an economic growth , and the largest since the first to the third quarter in 2005 . It was mainly because of the help from personal expenditures , capital expenditures , and steady exports . 
In addition , Japan 's Central Bank will also terminate its five - year - long extremely relaxed monetary policy in April , thus fostering an expectation for an economic boom in the financial market . 
With the slight improvement in the unemployment rate and wages from October to December , private consumption had increased by 0.8 percent . 
The Nikkei Index rose after the release of the GDP information . However , by morning closing it had dropped 0.74 percent . 
The Japanese yen fell after a short appreciation . The trading price lingered at around 118.15 Japanese yen to 1 U.S . dollar . 
