( Newspaper Digest ) Part - Time Workers and High School Graduates Become Major Forces of Hourly - Paid Work in Shanghai 
Xinhua News Agency , Beijing , February 7 . The " Guidance on the Current Standard for Hourly - Paid Wages in 2006 " issued by the Labor and Social Support Bureau of Shanghai City on February 6 , lists 120 occupations , which is 11 more than the number issued last time . The " wage levels " of the original positions are either increased or reduced . 
As an estimate made by related experts of the Labor and Social Support Bureau of Shanghai City , currently the hourly - paid workers in Shanghai are more than one million . 
As China Youth Journal reported , part - time workers and high school graduates are the major part of the team of hourly - paid labors . 
Through a direct survey of more than 8,000 hourly - paid workers , more than half of them are part - time workers , and their ratio is 51.1 % . 
Those part - time workers are generally well educated , and mainly do more technical work . For instance , the ratio of part - time workers in the translation occupation is as high as 81.7 % , and that in the gym business is 61.6 % . 
High income is one of the important reasons for many people to work at hourly - paid part - time jobs . 
As was learned , monthly income for some positions can reach up to several tens of thousands of Yuan , and it is difficult to find high - demand talents , such as simultaneous interpreters ; most hourly - paid workers ' monthly incomes can reach more than 2,000 Yuan , such as part - time financial workers , wedding ceremony managers , etc. 
One of the important reasons for the popularity of part - time workers for hourly wages is that those jobs suit individual interests and workers can learn more knowledge from those jobs . 
For instance , Mr. Gu , who is a manager of the Human Resources Unit at a company , uses several hours to handle business accounts for a foreign business agency every week . 
Mr. Gu thinks that the greatest benefit of a part - time job is to continuously renew his own knowledge , and has opportunities to know another field , and of course , a monthly income of 2,000 Yuan is also attractive to a certain extent . 
Since some positions for hourly - paid workers are low - skill ones , and their working patterns are flexible and free , they have gradually become popular among a lot of graduates who are looking for jobs . 14 % of hourly - paid workers are graduates from colleges and polytechnic schools in the last three years . 
" I did not want to do an hourly - paid job in the beginning . But several months later , I feel it is better than 9 to 5 work . " 
Xiao Huang 's job hunting is not that satisfying after he graduates from college . He eventually registers with a hotel and plays background music on a piano . 
" I am quite satisfied with my current work , 100 yuan per hour , and the environment is also good . What I should do now is to find several more hourly - paid jobs . " 
As has been learned , hourly - paid jobs have become an important path for those graduates who are looking for jobs to accumulate work experience , exercise their work skills , improve their communication skills , and enrich their social experience . 
Those graduates who work at hourly - paid jobs are mainly concentrated in positions that require more knowledge and skills , including translation positions , which require professional skills , and entertainment and performance positions , which require current popularity . These two kinds of positions are 22.1 % and 26.8 % , respectively , among those jobs that require more knowledge and skills . 
Some positions for hourly - paid workers do not require high skills , such as food promotion workers , merchandise handlers , and unemployed workers who are able to work through simple trainings . 
Data shows that those hourly - paid workers who used to be unemployed are 39 % of the total hourly - paid workers ; among them , workers who used to work in retail business are 68.4 % ; and those in restaurants and food businesses are 58.7 % . The hourly - paid jobs have become an important channel for unemployed workers to find their employment . 
