China Comes Up With an " Important Science and Research Plan " for Future 15 Years 
Xinhua News Agency , Beijing , February 9 ( reporter : Li Xing ) To promote China 's international competitive capacity , vigorously advance sustainable development , and realize a prioritized plan for surpassing ( developed countries ) , the " Outline Plan for the State 's Medium - and Long - Term Scientific and Technological Development ( 2006 to 2020 ) , " issued by the State Council on the 9th , has arranged four important plans for scientific studies . 
The four important scientific plans include protein studies , quantum adjustment and control studies , nano - studies , and growth and reproduction studies . 
The outline points out that protein science is the peak of life science that developed countries are fiercely competing for . 
In the next 15 years , China should focus on studying transcription repression histochemistry , protein histochemistry , metabolic histochemistry , structural biology , functions and interactions of protein biology , biology and systematic biology regarding protein calculation , methodology of protein studies and related application and basic studies , etc. 
At the same time , the outline thinks that quantum adjustment and control studies has an obvious forward - looking nature , and might significantly impact the economic development of human society to an extent that can hardly be assessed in 20 to 30 years . 
China should focus on studying the carrier , adjustment , and control rationales and methods of quantum communication , quantum calculation , the new quantum effect of constrained small quantum systems , quantum adjustment and control demonstration , and a new rationale and technical basis for quantum measurement , etc. 
Moreover , the outline points out that nano - technology has become the strategic selection for many countries to promote their core competitive capacity , and also is one of the fields for China to realize its surpassing development . 
In the next 15 years , China will focus on studying in this field , including controllable equipment , self - assembly , and functionalization of nano - material , nano - electronics , nano - biology , nano - medicine , nano - size demonstration and metrology , and applications of nano - material and technology in fields such as energy , the environment , information , medicine , etc. 
Since China 's population is growing on a large scale , there are many birth defects , a serious shortage of organs for transplants , and the aging peak is coming , it urgently needs to make breakthroughs and technological innovations in the scientific theories on reproduction and development . 
Based on the outline , from 2006 to 2020 , China will focus on studying stem cell reproduction , differentiation , adjustment , and control ; production , maturity , and fertilization of reproductive cells ; the mechanism of declination and degenerative pathological changes in human reproductive functions ; and the safety and ethics of assisting reproduction of stem cells , and stem cell technology , etc. 
